article.headline: Houston 85, McNeese State 72
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Andre Owens scored 26 points to lead Houston to an 85-72 victory over McNeese State on Friday night. Owens was 8-of-17 from the field, including 4-of-10 from 3-point range for Houston (2-1). He hit all six of his free throws. Lanny Smith added 15 points and had five assists. Edward Garriet led McNeese State (0-1) with 26 points, hitting 8-of-10 3-pointers. His eight 3-pointers tied a school record. The 85 points was the most by Houston since the Cougars defeated Tulane 85-81 on Feb. 19, 2002. Houston took advantage of 20 McNeese State turnovers, scoring 27 points. Houston led 32-26 at the half.
